Instruction.1: Hold the Barbell with both hands and kneel on the floor with your feet up
Instruction.2: Slowly roll the Barbell straight forward, stretching your body into a straight position.
Instruction.3: After a pause at the stretched position, start pulling yourself back to the starting position. This should be a slow and controlled movement.

Instruction.1: Hold the bar with a slightly wider than shoulder width grip. Push the bar up toward the ceiling and maintain that elbow extension.
Instruction.2: Flex your abs and sit-up. Aim to get your torso vertical while maintaining the barbell overhead.

Instruction.1: Start in a bench press position with your legs elevated. Try to keep your knees with a slight bend in them.
Instruction.2: Unrack the bar then initiate the rep.
Instruction.3: Bring the bar to your torso and tap your ribcage before pressing back to the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Start by lying flat on your back with your legs extended towards the landmine attachment and your arms overhead, holding the landmine barbell with both hands while engaging your core muscles by pressing your lower back into the ground and drawing your belly button in towards your spine.
Instruction.2: Lift your legs off the ground, keeping them together and straight, and simultaneously raise your upper body off the ground, reaching the landmine barbell away from your face.
Instruction.3: Hold this position for the desired duration, then carefully lower the barbell to the ground.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the ground and hold the end of the bar with your arms extended.
Instruction.2: Raise your back off the ground until you are sitting at a 90 degree angle.
Instruction.3: Then lower slowly back to the floor.

Instruction.1: Measure your hands by the markings on the bar to make sure you're even. Then throw your elbows underneath the bar.
Instruction.2: The bar should be set so high on your shoulders it digs into your neck a bit. Make sure to push your elbows up to the ceiling for the entire rep. To make sure you don't get too pitched forward.
Instruction.3: Use the squat stance you would use for a back or goblet squat. Push your hips back to initiate the squat. Break at the knees until you hit parallel depth.
Instruction.4: Squat back up to a standing position.

Instruction.1: Start in a bench press position with your feet planted on the bench and knees bent.
Instruction.2: Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, positioning your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.3: Lift the barbell off the rack and lower it to your chest, keeping your elbows close to your sides.
Instruction.4: Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms.

Instruction.1: Stand straight and hold the end of the Barbell
Instruction.2: Keep your hips and shoulders facing forward, bend to one side slowly
Instruction.3: Return to the upright position.
Instruction.4: Switch hands and repeat.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and holding a barbell at one side of your body, with your palms facing your thighs.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, bend at the hips and knees to lower the barbell down towards the ground.
Instruction.3: As the barbell reaches the ground, use your legs and glutes to push through your heels and extend your hips and knees to raise your body back to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat the movement for the desired number of reps, then switch sides and repeat the exercise with the barbell on the opposite side of your body.

Instruction.1: Set up the landmine attachment and load weight.
Instruction.2: Stand facing the landmine, holding the weight away from your chest.
Instruction.3: Step backward with one leg, lunge down while twisting your torso toward the front leg, return to starting position, and repeat on the other side.

Instruction.1: Kneel down facing the landmine with your knees hip-width apart and your back straight. Grasp the landmine barbell with both hands, interlacing your fingers and holding it above and slightly in front of your body.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, twist your torso to one side, rotating your arms and the landmine along with it. Pause briefly at the end of the twist, feeling the contraction in your oblique muscles.
Instruction.3: Slowly rotate back to the starting position, then twist to the opposite side, repeating the same motion.
Instruction.4: Repeat both sides of the rotation for the desired number of reps.

Instruction.1: Stand facing the landmine, with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. Grasp the landmine barbell with both hands, interlacing your fingers and holding it at chest height. Position your arms straight out in front of you, parallel to the floor, with your elbows slightly bent.
Instruction.2: While keeping your core engaged, rotate your torso and the landmine to one side. Twist through your waist, using your oblique muscles to generate the movement. Pivot on the ball of your opposite foot as you rotate away from it.
Instruction.3: Rotate back to the starting position, then perform the same movement in the opposite direction.
Instruction.4: Repeat for the desired number of reps.

Instruction.1: Start sitting on the ground facing the landmine attachment, holding the end of the bar in both hands slightly in front of and above your chest while holding your feet off the ground and knees bent.
Instruction.2: Bending your elbows as little as possible and keeping your core tight and feet elevated, lower the end of the bar with control to the ground on one side of your body, then contract your obliques to return the bar to the center. Repeat on the other side.
Instruction.3: Repeat for the desired number of reps.

Instruction.1: Hold the end of the bar. Start with a shoulder width stance.
Instruction.2: Bring both arms to one side and keep your elbows mostly extended.
Instruction.3: Rotate back and forth and try to resist twisting too much.

Instruction.1: Stand perpendicularly to the barbell with the end of the bar in front of your feet. Squat down and hold the end of the bar with your hand closer to the landmine attachment with your palm facing your body.
Instruction.2: Drive your feet into the ground to start the motion. As your legs fully extend, pull the bar upwards with your hand and start to rotate your torso in towards the landmine attachment. As you do so, bring your other hand up to the bar and switch your grip. Press through the bar to extend your arm all the way upright, pivoting your back foot to allow for more trunk rotation.
Instruction.3: Perform the movement in reverse to return to the starting position. Repeat for desired number of reps before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart with the bar on the ground at your side.
Instruction.2: Lift the bar to your side and walk for the allotted amount of time or distance.
Instruction.3: Set the bar down and switch sides.

Instruction.1: Hold the Ab Roller with both hands and kneel on the floor with your feet up and crossed.
Instruction.2: Slowly roll the ab roller straight forward, stretching your body into a straight position.
Instruction.3: After a pause at the stretched position, start pulling yourself back to the starting position. This should be a slow and controlled movement.

Instruction.1: Place your feet on the rower seat and get in to a hand plank position.
Instruction.2: Pull your knees to your chest and flex your abs.

Instruction.1: Place your feet on the rower seat and get in to a plank position.
Instruction.2: Pull your hips straight up toward the ceiling.
Instruction.3: Lower your hips until you're back in a plank position.

Instruction.1: Place your feet under the foot pads and grab the handles with your hands.
Instruction.2: Flex your spine and bring your upper and lower body together.

Instruction.1: Lay on a ball or a Bosu ball with your feet firmly planted on the floor.
Instruction.2: Lean all the way back until you feel a stretch in your abdomen.
Instruction.3: Crunch upwards and hold for a 1-2 count.
Instruction.4: Slowly return to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand upright.
Instruction.2: After completing the desired amount of reps with the left arm, switch to the right arm and lean to the left.
Instruction.3: Reach up with your left arm and then lean slowly to the right. Lean until a stretch is felt in the obliques.

Instruction.1: Stand upright.
Instruction.2: Reach with both hands upwards until you can interlock your fingers.
Instruction.3: With your hands above your head, lean back until a stretch is felt in the abdominals.

Instruction.1: Lay on your stomach on the floor with your forearms flat on the ground.
Instruction.2: Extend your elbows and push your upper body upwards.
Instruction.3: Push your upper body upwards until you feel a stretch in your abs, then return to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Start by lying on your back on a mat with your legs bent and feet flat on the ground.
Instruction.2: Hold a weight plate over your head with both hands, making sure to keep your arms straight.
Instruction.3: Engage your core and use your abdominal muscles to sit up, keeping the weight plate towards the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Get into a kneeling position with both forearms pressed into the ground.
Instruction.2: Place a weight plate on your back (or have a partner do it for you).
Instruction.3: Hold the plank for the allotted amount of time.

Instruction.1: Start in a kneeling position with your hands planted on the ground.
Instruction.2: Place a weight plate on your back or have a friend do it for you.
Instruction.3: Pick your knees up off the ground. Hold in this position with a flat back.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the ground with your arms extended over head holding a weight plate.
Instruction.2: Pick your upper back and your legs off the ground. Your body should be in a banana shape.

Instruction.1: Start by sitting on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground
Instruction.2: Engage your core muscles by pulling your belly button toward your spine.
Instruction.3: Slowly twist your upper body to the right, keeping your feet flat on the ground and your back straight.
Instruction.4: Hold for a second and then twist to the left, holding for another second.

Instruction.1: Start from a plank position. Place a plate on your back.
Instruction.2: Go to one elbow then the other. Try to avoid rocking back and forth.

Instruction.1: Stand with a plate extended away from your body. Elbows mostly extended.
Instruction.2: Rotate at the upper spine while keeping your lumbar spine in a neutral position.
Instruction.3: Do not let the plate go behind your body.

Instruction.1: Stand with a shoulder width stance. Begin with the plate near one of your quads.
Instruction.2: Rotate at your upper spine to engage the obliques.
Instruction.3: You can pivot your back foot to keep from generating too much torque at the knee.

Instruction.1: Step back with your right foot into a lunge position, both knees bent at 90 degrees.
Instruction.2: Twist your torso to the right, keeping the plate close to your chest.
Instruction.3: Push through your front foot to return to the starting position and repeat on the other side.

Instruction.1: Stand straight with the plate held at your side
Instruction.2: Keep your hips and shoulders facing forward, bend to one side slowly
Instruction.3: Return to the upright position.
Instruction.4: Switch hands and repeat

Instruction.1: Place forearms on Bosu, elbows under shoulders.
Instruction.2: Extend legs, keeping body straight.
Instruction.3: Hold the plank position, engaging core.

Instruction.1: Place hands on Bosu, shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Extend legs, keeping body straight.
Instruction.3: Hold the plank position, engaging core.

Instruction.1: Place both hands on Bosu, wider than shoulder-width.
Instruction.2: Perform a pushup, then walk hands to the other side.
Instruction.3: Perform another pushup, repeat back and forth.

WorkoutName: Bosu Ball Hand Sideplank Hip Abduction

Instruction.1: Set up the Smith machine bar at an appropriate height.
Instruction.2: Lie on your back beneath the bar, gripping it with your hands.
Instruction.3: Engage your core, lift your upper body toward the bar, and exhale.
Instruction.4: Lower your upper body back down in a controlled manner, inhaling.

Instruction.1: Put a hip thrust pad on the smith machine bar at neck height. Put both arms over the bar and pull your feet off the ground.
Instruction.2: Pull your knees to your chest and flex your abs.

WorkoutName: Smith Machine Reverse Crunch Hip Raise

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the ground. With your feet on the bar.
Instruction.2: Lift your hips off the ground.

Instruction.1: Lay on your side with your knees bent.
Instruction.2: Hold the bar extended over you.
Instruction.3: Lift yourself up by flexing your obliques.

Instruction.1: Stand beside the bar.
Instruction.2: Keep your hips and shoulders facing forward, bend to one side slowly
Instruction.3: Return to the upright position.
Instruction.4: Switch hands and repeat.

WorkoutName: Smith Machine Side Plank Up Down

Instruction.1: Start by lying on your side with your feet stacked on top of each other and the bar on your hip.
Instruction.2: Place your bottom elbow on the ground beneath your shoulder and engage your core to raise your hips off the ground.
Instruction.3: Your hips will do all the moving. Think, "hips up, hips down."

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the ground with your spine neutral. Extend you arms so your fists are pointed at the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Sit-up by flexing your abs. Continue to reach for the ceiling for the entire rep.

Instruction.1: Get into a plank position. Either from your knees or toes.
Instruction.2: Start with the DB by your right hand. Reach with your left and pull the dumbbell to your left arm. Then repeat with the right.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the ground with a dumbbell overhead.
Instruction.2: Pull your upper back and legs off the ground. Make a banana shape with your body.
Instruction.3: The dumbbell should be held in your hands and your ears should be between your biceps.

Instruction.1: Start by lying flat on your back with your feet flat on the floor and your knees bent.
Instruction.2: Hold a dumbbell over your clavicle.
Instruction.3: Engage your core muscles and lift your torso off the floor until your shoulders are a few inches off the ground.
Instruction.4: Lower yourself back down to the starting position, but avoid resting completely on the floor between reps.

Instruction.1: Start in a plank position. Hold one dumbbell.
Instruction.2: Raise the dumbbell straight out in front of you (I), at a 45 degree angle (Y), out to the side (T), and then bend at the elbow while raising (W).
Instruction.3: Going through IYTW counts as one rep.
Instruction.4: Make sure to keep your hips stable. If you're unable to, try performing this exercise from the knees.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the ground with a dumbbell. Point the soles of your shoes at the ceiling as well as the dumbbell.
Instruction.2: Reach for your feet with the dumbbell before bringing your spine back to the floor.

Instruction.1: Sit on the floor and flex your knees and hips to a 90 degree angle.
Instruction.2: Your feet should be hovering off the ground. (If that's too hard start with heels on the floor)
Instruction.3: Rotate your upper spine to engage your obliques.

Instruction.1: Take a half kneeling position. Start with the dumbbell by your knee on the side of the kneeling leg.
Instruction.2: Rotate at the upper spine, holding the dumbbell away from your body with nearly extended elbows.

Instruction.1: Start by getting into a plank position with a dumbbell in each hand. Your feet should be shoulder-width apart and your hands should be placed on the dumbbells, with your palms facing each other.
Instruction.2: From this starting position, row one dumbbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body and your core engaged.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position, and repeat on the other side.
Instruction.4: Make sure to keep your body straight and your hips level throughout the movement.

Instruction.1: Start in a high plank position with a pair of dumbbells positioned under your shoulders. Your hands should grip the dumbbells, palms facing each other.
Instruction.2: Keep your core engaged and your back straight as you row one dumbbell up towards your hip, keeping your elbow close to your body.
Instruction.3: Lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position and repeat on the other side.

Instruction.1: Stand with a shoulder width stance. Begin with the dumbbell near one of your quads.
Instruction.2: Rotate at your upper spine to engage the obliques.
Instruction.3: You can pivot your back foot to keep from generating too much torque at the knee.

Instruction.1: Start in a kneeling position with your shoulder blades pulled back.
Instruction.2: The dumbbell should begin by one of your hips.
Instruction.3: Rotate at the spine and bring the dumbbell from your hip, 180 degrees around your body. The dumbbell should land at eye level.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell overhead.
Instruction.2: From this starting position, bend to the side as far as you can while keeping your feet planted and your core engaged.

Instruction.1: Start by lying on your side with your feet stacked on top of each other and a dumbbell on your hip.
Instruction.2: Place your bottom elbow on the ground beneath your shoulder and engage your core to raise your hips off the ground.
Instruction.3: Your hips will do all the moving. Think, "hips up, hips down."

Instruction.1: Start by lying on your side with your feet stacked on top of each other and a dumbbell on your hip.
Instruction.2: Place your bottom hand on the ground beneath your shoulder and engage your core to raise your hips off the ground.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, hold the side plank position for the desired amount of time, making sure to keep your body straight and your hips level.

Instruction.1: Start by sitting on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. Hold a dumbbell in both hands with your arms extended straight in front of you.
Instruction.2: Twist your torso to the right, bringing the dumbbell towards the ground, then return to the center. Repeat on the left side, twisting to the left and bringing the dumbbell towards the ground.
Instruction.3: Continue this twisting motion, alternating sides, for the desired number of repetitions. Keep your core engaged and avoid swinging your arms to generate momentum.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart and place your right hand on the right hip.
Instruction.2: Hold a dumbbell with the left hand. Bend at the hips to the side.
Instruction.3: Make sure you don't start to lean forward to try and force a longer range of motion.

Instruction.1: Hold a dumbbell over one shoulder.
Instruction.2: Initiate the squat by pushing your hips back.
Instruction.3: Avoid doing any twisting. Try to keep your shoulders even.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back, holding a medicine ball overhead.
Instruction.2: Lift your shoulders and legs off the ground, engaging core.
Instruction.3: Hold the position while maintaining stability.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back, place a medicine ball between your extended arms and bent knees.
Instruction.2: Lower opposite arm and leg to floor, keeping back pressed against ground and medicine ball in place.
Instruction.3: Alternate sides, maintain core engagement, and repeat for desired reps or time.

WorkoutName: Medicine Ball Half Kneeling Wood Chopper

Instruction.1: Kneel, holding a medicine ball.
Instruction.2: Rotate torso and slam the ball diagonally down and across.
Instruction.3: Repeat the movement on the other side.

Instruction.1: Use a double handle attachment and set the cable all the way to the top.
Instruction.2: Face away from the cable tower and walk a few steps forward.
Instruction.3: Push your hips back, and flex your abs.
Instruction.4: Return to the starting standing position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Use a double handle attachment and set the cable all the way to the top.
Instruction.2: Walk a few steps forward then fall into a kneeling position.
Instruction.3: Push your hips back and flex your abs, then push hips forward until in the starting position.

Instruction.1: Use a rope attachment and set the cable all the way to the top.
Instruction.2: Walk a few steps forward then fall into a kneeling position.
Instruction.3: Push your hips back and flex your abs, then push hips forward until in the starting position.

Instruction.1: Use a rope attachment and set the cable all the way to the top.
Instruction.2: Walk a few steps forward then fall into a kneeling position.
Instruction.3: Push your hips back and flex your abs, then push hips forward until in the starting position.

Instruction.1: Set the cable at about nipple level. Use a handle attachment.
Instruction.2: Face sideways, then rotate your torso with your arms extended against the resistance.
Instruction.3: After completing your given number of reps, face the opposite direction and repeat.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment, set the cable at nipple level, walk a few steps away, and face sideways.
Instruction.2: Start with both hands on the handle and your fists against your chest.
Instruction.3: Press the handle forward until your elbows are fully extended, then pull the handle back to your chest.

WorkoutName: Cable Half Kneeling High To Low Wood Chopper

Instruction.1: Set the cable just over your head. Take a half kneeling position. Use a handle attachment.
Instruction.2: Face sideways, then rotate your torso with your arms extended against the resistance.
Instruction.3: After completing your given number of reps, face the opposite direction and repeat.

WorkoutName: Cable Half Kneeling Low To High Wood Chopper

Instruction.1: Set the cable at a low position. Take a half kneeling position. Use a handle attachment.
Instruction.2: Face sideways, then rotate your torso with your arms extended against the resistance.
Instruction.3: After completing your given number of reps, face the opposite direction and repeat.

Instruction.1: Set the cable at nipple level. Take a half kneeling position. Use a handle attachment.
Instruction.2: Face sideways, then rotate your torso with your arms extended against the resistance.
Instruction.3: After completing your given number of reps, face the opposite direction and repeat.

Instruction.1: Set the cable just over your head. Use a handle attachment.
Instruction.2: Face sideways, push the handle down until your elbow is extended. Flex your obliques until you feel a contraction.
Instruction.3: After completing your given number of reps, face the opposite direction and repeat.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment, set the cable at nipple level, walk a few steps away, and face sideways.
Instruction.2: Start with both hands on the handle and your fists against your chest.
Instruction.3: Press the handle forward until your elbows are fully extended, then rotate away from the cable stack.
Instruction.4: Then pull the handle back to your chest.

Instruction.1: Set the cable at the bottom of the stack. Use a handle attachment.
Instruction.2: Face sideways, grab the handle, lean away from the cable.
Instruction.3: After completing your given number of reps, face the opposite direction and repeat.

Instruction.1: Grasp the TRX handles with both hands, keeping your arms extended and your shoulders away from your ears.
Instruction.2: Keep your abs engaged, roll forward onto your toes, and extend your arms in front of you.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower your body down to the ground, keeping your arms straight and your abs engaged.
Instruction.4: When your head gets between your arms, pause for a moment and then use your abs to pull your body back up to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Lie face down on the ground and place your forearms on the ground directly under your shoulders.
Instruction.2: With your feet in the stirrups, kick both feet into the TRX straps and hold the handles above your head.
Instruction.3: Tighten your abs, glutes, and legs to form a straight line from your head to your feet.

Instruction.1: Start by facing away from the TRX straps and placing your feet in the TRX handles with your palms on the ground.
Instruction.2: Lift your knees off the ground to begin the set.
Instruction.3: Engage your core and maintain this position for the desired amount of time, holding a steady plank.

Instruction.1: Place your feet in the TRX stirrups and get in to a hand plank position.
Instruction.2: Pull your knees to your chest and flex your abs.

Instruction.1: Start in a plank position with the TRX straps adjusted to mid-calf length. Place your feet in the TRX stirrups.
Instruction.2: Keep your abs engaged, and bring one knee towards your chest while keeping the other leg extended behind you.
Instruction.3: Switch legs, bringing the opposite knee towards your chest while keeping your abs engaged and your back straight.

Instruction.1: Place your feet in the stirrups and get in to a plank position.
Instruction.2: Pull your hips straight up toward the ceiling.
Instruction.3: Lower your hips until you're back in a plank position.

Instruction.1: Lie on your side with your legs straight and your feet resting in the TRX foot cradles.
Instruction.2: Prop yourself up on your forearm and engage your core to maintain a straight line from your head to your feet.

Instruction.1: Place your feet in the TRX stirrups and get in to a hand plank position.
Instruction.2: Pull both knees to your right elbow.
Instruction.3: Extend your legs back to the starting position, then pull both knees to the left elbow.

Instruction.1: Hold the attachment with both hands and take a kneeling position.
Instruction.2: Rotate across your body.

WorkoutName: Core Stability 1 Crosslateral Limb Raise 4Pt Position

Instruction.1: Bring yourself to the 4 point position (on all fours)
Instruction.2: 90° angles at hips and shoulder and neutral spine
Instruction.3: Raise opposite limbs till they are parallel to the ground
Instruction.4: Hold for a split second and bring back to starting position

WorkoutName: Core Stability 2 Opposite Shoulder Tap 4Pt Position

Instruction.1: Bring yourself to the 4 point position (on all fours). 90° angles at hips and shoulder and neutral spine.
Instruction.2: Lift your knees slightly off the ground supporting your weight on palms and toes.
Instruction.3: Maintain a toe placement roughly at shoulder width (the wider the leg stance the easier the exercise - the narrower the stance the more difficult it becomes.
Instruction.4: Tap your opposite shoulder with your fingertips.

WorkoutName: Core Stability 4 Crosslateral Limb Raise Push Up Position

Instruction.1: Bring yourself to a strict push-up position
Instruction.2: Maintain a toe placement roughly at shoulder width (the wider the leg stance the easier the exercise - the narrower the stance the more difficult it becomes.
Instruction.3: Tap your opposite shoulder with your fingertips.
Instruction.4: Do not tilt or shift your hips. Do not round or arch your back.

WorkoutName: Core Stability 5 Crosslateral Limb Raise Into Knee Elbow Tuck Push Up Position

Instruction.1: Bring yourself to a strict push-up position
Instruction.2: Raise opposite limbs till they are parallel to the ground
Instruction.3: Hold for a split second and then try to bring your elbow to your opposite knee by driving both towards the centre of the body.
Instruction.4: Spine might curve slightly but you should not shift your hips during the movement.

WorkoutName: Core Stability Regression Crosslateral Limb Raise Push Up Position

Instruction.1: Bring yourself to a strict push-up position
Instruction.2: Tap the hand of the working arm on the ground to find your balance. Raise opposite limbs till they are parallel to the ground
Instruction.3: Hold for a split second and then try to bring your elbow to your opposite knee by driving both towards the centre of the body.
Instruction.4: Spine might curve slightly but you should not shift your hips during the movement.

Instruction.1: Lay on your back. Extend your straight arms above the chest and raise your bent knees till they are over your hips.
Instruction.2: Lower limbs of the same side towards the ground. You can feel the ground but do not rest on or tap off of the ground.
Instruction.3: Maintain a flat lower back throughout the movement (lower back should be in contact with the ground).

Instruction.1: Lie on your back. Raise your legs but bend your knees
Instruction.2: Keep a 90° angle at hips and knees. Lower your toes to the ground without bending your knees
Instruction.3: Make sure you maintain a flat lower back against the ground throughout the movement.

Instruction.1: Support your weight on your forearms and toes (plank).
Instruction.2: Allow your upper back to sink in between the shoulder blades.
Instruction.3: Push your elbows into the ground and slightly forward, and move the shoulder blades away from the spine.

Instruction.1: Support your weight on your forearms and toes (plank).
Instruction.2: Allow your upper back to sink in between the shoulder blades.
Instruction.3: Push your elbows into the ground and slightly forward, and move the shoulder blades away from the spine.

WorkoutName: Crosslateral Core Stabilisation Unilateral Load Kettlebell

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and holding a kettlebell at one side of your body, with your palms facing your thighs.
Instruction.2: Hing forward with a flat back and lift the kettlebell.
Instruction.3: Hold the kettlebell at your side and make sure to not lean to one side.

Instruction.1: Sit on your heels and reach out your arms on the floor while pressing the chest towards the ground.
Instruction.2: Bend your spine towards one side and reach over with your arms.
Instruction.3: Do the same on the opposite side.

Instruction.1: While seated on a bench, place your palms on the bench by your sides
Instruction.2: Palm placement should allow room for the fingers to grip the edge of the bench
Instruction.3: Try to lift your bodyweight off the bench by pushing the palms into the bench
Instruction.4: Lockout your elbows and repeat or hold isometrically

Instruction.1: While seated on a bench, place your palms on the bench by your sides
Instruction.2: Palm placement should allow room for the fingers to grip the edge of the bench
Instruction.3: Try to lift your bodyweight off the bench by pushing the palms into the bench
Instruction.4: Lockout your elbows and hold isometrically

Instruction.1: Lay flat on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the ground, about a foot from your lower back.
Instruction.2: Place your fingertips on your temples with your palms facing out.
Instruction.3: Draw your belly into the base of your spine to engage the muscles, then raise your head and shoulders off the floor. Return to starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Lay on your back with your arms palms down on either side.
Instruction.2: Keep your legs together and as straight as possible.
Instruction.3: Slowly raise your legs to a 90° angle, pause at this position, or as high as you can reach your legs, and then slowly lower your legs back down.
Instruction.4: Duration of these movements should be slow so that you do not utilize momentum, enabling you to get the most out of the exercise.

Instruction.1: Place forearms on the ground with your elbows bent at a 90° angle aligned beneath your shoulders, with your arms parallel at shoulder-width.
Instruction.2: Your feet should be together, with only your toes touching the floor.
Instruction.3: Lift your belly off the floor and form a straight line from your heels to the crown of your head and hold.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar and hang, your body still and your legs straight.
Instruction.2: Slowly draw your knees up to your chest
Instruction.3: Once you have raised your knees as high as possible, lower your legs and repeat. Duration of these movements should be slow so that you do not utilize momentum, enabling you to get the most out of the exercise.

Instruction.1: Start in a hand plank position and walk your hands further out until your ears are between your biceps.
Instruction.2: Hold in this position for the allotted amount of time.
Instruction.3: Make sure you keep a flat back for the whole set.

Instruction.1: Start in a kneeling position with your hands planted on the ground.
Instruction.2: Pick your knees up off the ground. Hold in this position with a flat back.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the ground with your arms extended over head.
Instruction.2: Pick your upper back and your legs off the ground. Your body should be in a banana shape.
Instruction.3: Hold in this position.

Instruction.1: To perform a bodyweight mountain climber, start in a plank position with your hands placed directly under your shoulders.
Instruction.2: Bring your right knee towards your chest, keeping your foot close to your hand. Quickly switch legs, bringing your left knee towards your chest.
Instruction.3: Continue this movement, alternating legs, at a quick pace for a set amount of time or repetitions.

Instruction.1: Hover your heels just off the ground.
Instruction.2: Stick your chest out and maintain a flat back. Make all the movement happen at your mid and upper spine.
Instruction.3: Point your chest to the left, then rotate at the spine until your chest is pointed right.

Instruction.1: Start standing with your feet hip-width apart. Lower your body into a squat position, placing your hands on the ground in front of you.
Instruction.2: Quickly jump your feet back into a plank position, keeping your body in a straight line from your head to your toes.
Instruction.3: Perform a push-up, keeping your core tight and your elbows close to your body.
Instruction.4: Jump your feet back towards your hands, and then jump up into the air, reaching your arms overhead.
Instruction.5: Land softly and immediately lower your body back into the squat position to repeat the movement.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back.
Instruction.2: Bend knees, hands behind head.
Instruction.3: Twist torso, touch elbow to opposite knee. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Start on hands and knees.
Instruction.2: Extend right arm and left leg.
Instruction.3: Hold for a few seconds, then switch sides.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back, arms extended upward, legs raised with knees bent.
Instruction.2: Lower opposite arm and leg to floor, keeping back pressed against ground.
Instruction.3: Alternate sides, maintain core engagement, and repeat for desired reps or time.

Instruction.1: Start in a hand plank position and walk your elbows further out until your ears are between your biceps.
Instruction.2: Hold in this position for the allotted amount of time.
Instruction.3: Make sure you keep a flat back for the whole set.

Instruction.1: Sit in a v position.
Instruction.2: Pull legs and torso together.
Instruction.3: Extend back into the starting position.

Instruction.1: Lie on back, bosu elevated toward the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Sit up, engaging core muscles.
Instruction.3: Lower back down to complete one situp.

Instruction.1: Start from a kneeling plank position.
Instruction.2: Go to one elbow then the other. Try to avoid rocking back and forth.

Instruction.1: Start from a plank position.
Instruction.2: Go to one elbow then the other. Try to avoid rocking back and forth.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back, legs bent and lifted off the ground.
Instruction.2: Lower one leg to the ground until your foot taps the ground, keep your other leg up.
Instruction.3: Alternate sides for the prescribed amount of reps.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back, knees bent, feet flat.
Instruction.2: Reach right hand to right heel.
Instruction.3: Switch sides, left hand to left heel. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back, arms by sides, legs straight.
Instruction.2: Lift one leg to a 45-degree angle.
Instruction.3: Lower leg, lift opposite leg; alternate smoothly.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back, knees bent, feet flat on the floor.
Instruction.2: Raise both knees towards your chest.
Instruction.3: Lower back down without touching the floor; repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Grip bar, hang with arms extended, body straight.
Instruction.2: Engage core, lift knees towards chest.
Instruction.3: Lower legs back down, maintain controlled movement.

Instruction.1: Grip bar, hang with arms extended, body straight.
Instruction.2: Engage core, lift knees towards chest.
Instruction.3: Hold that position for the specified amount of time.

Instruction.1: Perform a reverse crunch and then kick your legs up toward the ceiling.
Instruction.2: With your hips and knees extended, lower yourself slowly back to the start position.

Instruction.1: Begin in an elbow plank position with your core engaged.
Instruction.2: Bring your right knee towards your right elbow.
Instruction.3: Return to plank, then switch legs quickly. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back, knees bent, hands behind head.
Instruction.2: Crunch up, flexing the spine and your abs.

Instruction.1: Lay on your back with knees bent and your feet together.
Instruction.2: Keep your arms extended overhead. Swing your arms to generate some momentum and sit up.

Instruction.1: Begin in a plank position, hands under shoulders, feet together.
Instruction.2: Jump feet forward, landing outside hands in a low squat.
Instruction.3: Explode back to plank, repeat continuously for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on your back with both hands over one leg.
Instruction.2: Reach toward your knee flexing your abs and obliques.
Instruction.3: Do the prescribed amount of reps, then switch sides.

Instruction.1: Start in a plank position with hands under shoulders.
Instruction.2: Jump one foot forward, switch legs mid-air.
Instruction.3: Alternate legs quickly, maintaining a steady plank.

Instruction.1: To perform a bodyweight mountain climber, start in a plank position with your hands placed directly under your shoulders.
Instruction.2: Bring your right knee towards your chest, keeping your foot close to your hand. Quickly switch legs, bringing your left knee towards your chest.
Instruction.3: Continue this movement, alternating legs, at a slow pace for a set amount of time or repetitions.

Instruction.1: Start in a plank position with hands directly under shoulders.
Instruction.2: Drive knees toward left elbow.
Instruction.3: Go back to starting position, then drive knees to right elbow, mimicking a zigzag slalom motion.

Instruction.1: Lift both legs off the ground.
Instruction.2: Bring both legs outward, then cross both legs over one another.
Instruction.3: Alternating which leg goes on top.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back, hands under your buttocks or on the ground for support.
Instruction.2: Lift legs off the ground, alternate crossing them in a scissor motion.

Instruction.1: Grasp the rings, keeping your arms extended and your shoulders away from your ears.
Instruction.2: Keep your abs engaged, roll forward onto your toes, and extend your arms in front of you.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower your body down toward the ground, keeping your arms straight and your abs engaged.
Instruction.4: When your head gets between your arms, pause for a moment and then use your abs to pull your body back up to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Perform a reverse crunch and then kick your legs up toward the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Flex at the hips and knees until your hips land back on the bench, then kick your legs back out to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start in a plank position.
Instruction.2: Raise your arm out in front of you.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position, then raise the opposing arm.
Instruction.4: Make sure to keep your hips stable. If you're unable to, try performing this exercise from the knees.

Instruction.1: Start in a plank position, hands under shoulders, body straight.
Instruction.2: Jump feet wide, then back together, like a jumping jack.
Instruction.3: Keep core tight, maintain plank form, repeat for desired time or reps.

Instruction.1: Hang from a bar with arms fully extended.
Instruction.2: Lift legs to form an "L" shape.
Instruction.3: Hold for allotted amount of time keeping your abs flexed.

Instruction.1: Start by lying flat on your back on a ball with your feet flat on the floor and your knees bent.
Instruction.2: Engage your core muscles and flex your spine until you feel your abs contract.

Instruction.1: Place feet on a stability ball, hands on the floor in a push-up position.
Instruction.2: Lower your chest toward the floor, then push up while tucking knees toward your chest.
Instruction.3: Extend legs back to starting position, maintaining control and stability throughout the movement.

Instruction.1: Start in a plank position with your feet on a stability ball and hands on the floor.
Instruction.2: Engage your core and tuck your knees toward your chest, rolling the ball forward carefully.
Instruction.3: Extend your legs back to the starting position, maintaining balance and control throughout the movement.

Instruction.1: Place your feet on the ball and get in to a plank position.
Instruction.2: Pull your hips straight up toward the ceiling.
Instruction.3: Lower your hips until you're back in a plank position.

Instruction.1: Kneel behind a stability ball, place forearms on top, and engage your core muscles.
Instruction.2: Lift knees, balance on toes, and slowly move forearms in small controlled circles.
Instruction.3: Maintain a stable torso, avoid excessive movement, and reverse direction after several rotations.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back, holding a stability ball between your feet, arms extended overhead.
Instruction.2: Engage your core, lift your legs and arms, passing the ball from feet to hands.
Instruction.3: Lower arms and legs back down, then repeat, passing the ball back to feet.

Instruction.1: Lie on your back, legs extended, stability ball between your feet, arms out for support.
Instruction.2: Engage your core, lift your legs, and rotate them side to side in a controlled motion.
Instruction.3: Keep your upper body stable, move slowly, and return to center before switching directions.

Instruction.1: Start with your elbow and hip on the ground. Either neutral fist or flat hand on the ground.
Instruction.2: Begin in a side plank position, and then drop your hips to the floor.
Instruction.3: Pull your hips back to the ceiling to finish the rep.

Instruction.1: Begin in an elbow side plank position.
Instruction.2: Reach for the ceiling with your off hand.
Instruction.3: Rotate at the mid and upper spine and reach through the open space between the floor and your torso.
Instruction.4: Reach backwards, and then rotate back into the starting position.

Instruction.1: Press your elbow into the floor.
Instruction.2: Pick your hips up off the ground and maintain this position for the allotted amount of time.
Instruction.3: Make sure you don't let your chest fall forward or backward.

Instruction.1: Press your hand into the ground and pick up your hip off the ground.
Instruction.2: Open your chest and maintain this position for the allotted amount of time.

Instruction.1: Start in a side plank position.
Instruction.2: Reach your top arm under your body.
Instruction.3: Return to the plank position.

Instruction.1: Lie on your side, knees bent, hands behind head.
Instruction.2: Bring your elbow towards your knees and flex your obliques.

Instruction.1: Lie on your side, legs straight, hand behind head.
Instruction.2: Lift both legs and upper body simultaneously.
Instruction.3: Squeeze obliques, then lower back down. Repeat on both sides.

Instruction.1: Lie on back, arms out, legs together.
Instruction.2: Lift legs to 90 degrees.
Instruction.3: Rotate legs side to side, keeping shoulders grounded.

Instruction.1: Start on all fours then bring your chest to the ground. Place one hand on the ground in front of you. The other hand behind your head/ear.
Instruction.2: On the side of the hand that is behind your head, rotate until your elbow is pointed at the ceiling and then hold this position.

Instruction.1: Lie sideways on a stability ball, feet anchored, hands behind head, core engaged.
Instruction.2: Crunch sideways by contracting obliques, bringing your upper body toward your hip.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on your back with straight legs and hold the kettle bell above your chest at arms length.
Instruction.2: Draw your belly into the base of your spine to engage the muscles, then raise your head and shoulders off the floor with the kettlebell raised at arms length above your chest.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Sit on the floor with your legs bent, knees together and feet raised slightly off the floor.
Instruction.2: Starting on one side and sitting up straight with your core muscles engaged, lift the kettlebell off the floor with both hands and bring it across your body to the other side, rotating your chest towards the floor as you do so.
Instruction.3: Tap the kettlebell lightly on the floor and bring the kettlebell back across your body to the starting position, rotating your chest towards the floor.
Instruction.4: Repeat, keeping the legs bent and feet raised throughout the exercise.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart. Hold the kettlebell in one hand and extend your arm above your head.
Instruction.2: Keeping your legs straight and the kettlebell above your head, lower the relaxed arm towards the ground, twisting your body towards the side of the raised arm.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting potion, tilt your pelvis forward and repeat.

Instruction.1: Hold kettlebells in front rack.
Instruction.2: Step back and lunge diagonally.

Instruction.1: Grab a kettlebell.
Instruction.2: Lie on your back, lift legs & shoulders off floor.
Instruction.3: Hold kettlebell above your head, engage core, and maintain position.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart. Hold the kettlebell in your bottom hand and extend the other arm above your head.
Instruction.2: Keeping your legs straight and the kettlebell inside your thigh, lower the kettlebell towards the ground, twisting your body towards the side of the raised arm.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position, tilt your pelvis forward and repeat.

Instruction.1: Start with kettlebells in front rack.
Instruction.2: Step forward into lunge.
Instruction.3: Return to starting position.

Instruction.1: Hold kettlebell in front rack.
Instruction.2: Step sideways into a lunge position.
Instruction.3: Return to start position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Start with kettlebell in front rack.
Instruction.2: Step back into lunge.
Instruction.3: Return to start position.

WorkoutName: Kettlebell Front Rack Single Arm Lateral Lunge

Instruction.1: Hold kettlebell in front rack.
Instruction.2: Step sideways, lunge.

WorkoutName: Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Forward Lunge
Kettlebell Single Arm Front Rack Step Up

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a step or bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a kettlebell at one shoulder.
Instruction.2: Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pushing off your foot to raise your body up onto the bench.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart and hold the kettle bell with both hands against your hip.
Instruction.2: Keeping your arms straight, swing the kettlebell upwards and across your body towards your shoulder, raising the kettlebell to head height rotating your hips as you do so.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with kettlebell between legs.
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, grab kettlebell, pull to chest and rotate at the torso

Instruction.1: Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and holding a kettlebell at one side of your body, with your palms facing your thighs.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, bend at the hips and knees to lower the kettlebell down towards the ground.
Instruction.3: As the kettlebell reaches the ground, use your legs and glutes to push through your heels and extend your hips and knees to raise your body back to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeat the movement for the desired number of reps, then switch sides and repeat the exercise with the kettlebell on the opposite side of your body.

Instruction.1: Standing straight with a kettlebell in one hand, walk for a specified distance or duration.
Instruction.2: Stay upright and don't lean to one side.

Instruction.1: Place the band at the highest anchor point you have available. Grab both ends of the band and fall into a kneeling position.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back flexing at the spine.
Instruction.3: Squeeze your abs and then extend at the hips and spine back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Place the band at an anchor point that is shoulder height. Take a few steps away until the band is taut.
Instruction.2: Start with your fingers interlocked around the band and your fists connected to your chest.
Instruction.3: Extend at the elbows pressing the band away from your body until your elbows are fully extended.

Instruction.1: Lie down on your back with your feet hip-distance apart and your knees bent.
Instruction.2: Place your hands on the floor beside your head, fingertips pointing towards your shoulders.
Instruction.3: Push your feet and hands into the floor, lift your hips up and straighten your arms.
Instruction.4: Lift your chest towards the ceiling and hold the pose for a few breaths before lowering back down.

Instruction.1: Start prone, hands under shoulders.
Instruction.2: Inhale, lift chest, arch back.
Instruction.3: Elongate neck, gaze up. Breathe, hold. Release, exhale.

WorkoutName: Gate Pose Variation Arm Extended on Side

Instruction.1: Start on your knees and extend your right leg out to the side.
Instruction.2: Raise your right arm above your head and reach towards the left side of the room.
Instruction.3: Gently bend your body to the left side and rest your left hand on your left thigh.
Instruction.4: Look up towards your right hand and hold the pose for a few breaths before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Sit on the floor with your legs extended in front of you.
Instruction.2: Bend your right knee and bring your heel towards your perineum.
Instruction.3: Place your left hand on the outside of your right knee and twist your body to the right.
Instruction.4: Reach your right hand towards your left foot and look up towards the ceiling. Hold the pose for a few breaths before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Sit comfortably on the floor with your legs crossed.
Instruction.2: Inhale and raise your right arm above your head.
Instruction.3: As you exhale, bend your body to the left side and rest your left hand on the ground.
Instruction.4: Look up towards the ceiling and hold the pose for a few breaths. Then switch sides and repeat the pose on the other side.

Instruction.1: Lie down on your back with your arms stretched out to your sides.
Instruction.2: Bend your right knee and bring it towards your chest.
Instruction.3: Slowly twist your body to the left side, bringing your right knee across your body towards the ground on the left side.
Instruction.4: Look towards your right hand and hold the pose for a few breaths before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Start in a downward facing dog position.
Instruction.2: Shift your weight onto your left hand and foot, and lift your right leg towards the ceiling.
Instruction.3: Slowly bend your right knee and shift your weight onto your right hand as you open up your chest towards the ceiling.
Instruction.4: Look towards your right hand and hold the pose for a few breaths before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of a low box.
Instruction.2: Bring one foot to the edge of the box and alternate as quickly as possible.
Instruction.3: Only lightly tap your feet to the box.

Instruction.1: Do a light hop and split your stance.
Instruction.2: Land lightly on your toes, and then bring the opposing leg forward.

Instruction.1: Bring one leg forward and then the other.
Instruction.2: Bring the original leg backwards and then the other.

Instruction.1: Leap sideways, land on right foot, left leg behind to the side.
Instruction.2: Drop into a single-leg burpee, right leg only, hands to ground.
Instruction.3: Return to standing on right, leap sideways to left, repeat with left leg.
